  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing the Community Policing Approach in Kirkuk and Anbar, Iraq</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project expands the community policing (CP) approach within the Kirkuk and Anbar governorates, building on the intervention carried out over the past years, to facilitate a more structured and therefore sustainable engagement between law enforcement officials and communities, so that they may jointly address safety and security issues affecting the communities. The increased interactions rebuild trust between law enforcement officials and communities and thereby contribute to increased peace, security and stability in Kirkuk and Anbar. IOM capitalises on its already established presence in both governorates and its close working relationship with the Ministry of Interior (MoI) to increase the capacity of law enforcement officials and institutions to engage with communities.  The project will also contribute to mainstreaming the CP approach across the law enforcement sector and strengthen the abilities of communities and civil society to engage with security actors.</narrative>
  </description>
